---

With #4195, we're now able to write 

```ts
@OneToOne('Profile')
@ManyToOne('User','photos')
@ManyToMany('Category')
```

instead of

```ts
@OneToOne(type => Profile)
@ManyToOne(type => User, user => user.photos)
@ManyToMany(type => Category)
```

which can prevent circular dependency issues in browser applications (as described in #4190).

However, there are still a few things that need to be improved:

#### Minification (e.g. UglifyJS) support

Currently, when using the `@OneToOne('Profile')` approach, `'Profile'` must exactly match the targets class name. This would stop working as soon as the code is minified, because class names are rewritten, but strings are not.

I would suggest to introduce a new `targetName` property to `EntityOptions` which TypeORM then would use instead of the constructor name:

```ts
@Profile({
  targetName: 'myProfile'
})
export class Photo {

  //...

}
```

The target name then has to be passed to the relation decorators:

```ts
@OneToOne('myProfile')
```

I'll submit a PR for this soon (hopefully mid next week).

